<br>
Stuns still have range limitations. There aren't many &quot;pally&quot; items that give extended spell range. But, with a long range bow and long range arrows, I can pull/tag from further away then I could with a stun, even with only 70 skill max. If I feel I need a stun to maintain aggro (I'd hope that I'd be handing off to a warrior instead) then I can hit it with one as it comes roaring in. This is a technique I've actually used many times to great success. I even have a knack for stunning mobs just before they hit melee range, which allows for the appropriate person to walk up and smack it 2-3 times before it gets to swing. (This also can allow for slows and malos to land.)<br>
<br>
I agree that if you're looking at stats only, then it shouldn't be limited to one class. (Although, you must admit that the stats would be $$ for pal/sk!) Rangers and warriors can have higher archery and can crit with a bow, so the archery damage is greater with them, but there's something to be said for a pally/sk having one. Any ranger I've ever known goes after the best bow they can find, and keeps it equipped. Because of our skill cap, pally's rarely look at this technique. But, it actually benefits a pally to have a bow like this. Otherwise, he has to put an idol in his range slot to buff up stats he needs. That's fine if you were never asked to pull or tag.... but I for one have been asked to do so quite often.<br>
<br>
I'll quit ranting now, but I will leave with one more item of thought...  Read the comments below the item. From what I can see, most of the rangers were bitching that there was no archery mod on this item, and would rather seek out one that did.<br>
